Signal processing for the second stimulation frequency

Scenario description This scenario is used for training of the Common Spatial Pattern filters. These enable you to use any set of electrodes and will automatically select the best combination of them for you. By default the dimension of the CSP filters is 2. If you use many electrodes you may want to raise this value to get even better precision. For the detailed description and experimental protocol, please refer to the SSVEP Scenario documentation on the OpenViBE website. note: the classifiers go to the folder where the scenario xml is located (${Player_ScenarioDirectory}/classifiers/).
You can browse each box' documentation by selecting the box and pressing F1
